From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Drawless Chess <engine@drawless.invalid>
Date: Tue, 14 Jul 2026 04:15:00 -0500
Subject: [PATCH] Fix stochastic rounding for negative Elo skill levels

Fairy-Stockfish converts low UCI_Elo values to fractional negative skill
levels. C++ integer conversion truncates those values toward zero, leaving a
negative remainder that can never satisfy the probabilistic round-up test.
Use floor as the lower endpoint so the two adjacent integer levels are chosen
with the intended probabilities and their mean matches the requested Elo.
---
 src/search.cpp | 5 +++--
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/src/search.cpp b/src/search.cpp
index 5f6465e..dff3513 100644
--- a/src/search.cpp
+++ b/src/search.cpp
@@ -370,8 +370,9 @@ void Thread::search() {
                                                 : shiftedElo / 143.4 + std::pow(shiftedElo / 500, 5),
                                  -20.0, 20.0) :
                         double(Options["Skill Level"]);
-  int intLevel = int(floatLevel) +
-                 ((floatLevel - int(floatLevel)) * 1024 > rng.rand<unsigned>() % 1024  ? 1 : 0);
+  int lowerLevel = int(std::floor(floatLevel));
+  int intLevel = lowerLevel +
+                 ((floatLevel - lowerLevel) * 1024 > rng.rand<unsigned>() % 1024  ? 1 : 0);
   Skill skill(intLevel);
 
   // When playing with strength handicap enable MultiPV search that we will
-- 
2.50.1

